echoing expanse, once a wealthy religious order's sanctum.  Remnants of their
theology remain in beautiful carvings and inscriptions in limestone walls and
pillars.  The graceful vaulted white limestone ceiling is decorated by
thousands of tiny embedded ultramarine-hued lapis, creating a glinting inverted
starfield.  Soft glowing lamps are fixed atop each pillar, casting their light
upon the polished surfaces of the marble floors and throwing dark shadows
behind the rows of pillars.  Lightly stained in the gray marble, the dark blue
image of a rearing fox is drawn where the pews of the sanctuary once sat.  
Outside the rows of pillars, some of the limestone pews remain, facing inwards
to the hall like audience seating.  Huge glazed stained glass windows line the
outer walls behind the pews, many of them dark blue or gray, allowing in little
light and giving the hall a rather somber mood.  At the east end of the hall, a
huge arch opens the hall to the rotunda and the remainder of the cathedral.  
From that end, the altar can cleary be seen on the other end, a low marble dais
with several blue throne-like seatings.    
